text: The 2015 Spanish general election was held on Sunday, 20 December 2015, to elect the 11th Cortes Generales of the Kingdom of Spain. All 350 seats in the Congress of Deputies were up for election, as well as 208 of 266 seats in the Senate. This election represented the end of the two-party system in Spain, as the new parties Podemos and Ciudadanos appeared. The result was a fragmented parliament in which no party had a majority. ==Notes== Category:2010s elections in Spain Category:2015 elections Category:Spanish general elections
title: 2015 Spanish general election
